.:: Puzzle 6x3-Level-2-2::.
The people have 3 different jobs:  journalist, police-officer, chef
The people's birthday is in 3 different months: july, november, february
The people perfer 3 different movie-genres: crime, documentary, drama
The people use 3 different means of transport: snowmobile, subway, ship
3 different games are played: snooker, monopoly, backgammon
The people prefer 3 different music-genres: funk, r&b, soul
1. the police-officer is on the left of the journalist##1
2. the person playing snooker is on the left of the fan of funk##1
3. the fan of r&b is on the left of the person who's birthday is in july##1
4. the person playing snooker is on the right of the person watching drama movies##1
5. the journalist is on the left of the person driving the subway##1
6. the person who's birthday is in february is between the person driving the ship and the chef##2
7. the person watching documentary movies is between the person watching drama movies and the person playing backgammon##2

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1     |      2      |    3     |
| Job      | police-officer     | journalist        | chef      |
| Birthday          | november    | february       | july  |
| Movie-Genre   | drama     | documentary | crime    |
| Transport   | ship | snowmobile   | subway    |
| Game           | monopoly      | snooker  | backgammon      |
| Music-Genre         | soul    | r&b      | funk |

